translation_en:
You are the imperishable, the supreme to be known;  
you are the ultimate resting place of this universe;  
you are the undying guardian of eternal dharma;  
you, I hold, are the everlasting person.

Into you these hosts of gods are entering;  
some, in fear, with folded hands, praise you;  
the hosts of great seers and the perfected, crying 'all hail,'  
extol you with abundant hymns.

You are the primal god, the ancient person, the supreme resting place of this universe;  
you are the knower and the known, the highest abode;  
by you the universe is pervaded, O you of endless forms.
